item.description:
Rjrasva (द्रष्टुं नोद्यम्) In Edo era, Eastern Japan had low TFR(or more accurately infant survival) rates due to infanticide&amp; abortion. Depop was serious so by late Edo there was pregnancy surveillance, subsidies, &amp; immigration (from domains without this issue)
Which is y it makes me laugh when people just project current trends linearly abt some &ldquo;human or Japanese or Korean extinction&rdquo; while confusing correlation with causation &amp;
underlying all this is the assumption that industrial civ will last forever because as Julian Simon taught us: &ldquo;there may well be other suns elsewhere&rdquo; &amp; human ingenuity will help turn copper into lead or as most people believe: there is infinite coal, oil, gas, copper on earth because why wouldn&rsquo;t there be?
